body:
Check what is happening in Scaler this week!
 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ 

This week looks super packed with knowledge and resources which will help you inch closer to your dream job. Explore and upskill with Scaler!

Register and attend a live session Learn, Apply, Win happening on 11th November, Thursday, at 8 PM IST, to understand key concepts on Arrays, which is essential to crack top product companies that you dream to work at.

Paridhi Gupta is a SDE and Instructor at Scaler. Loved by her students, she is one of the top-rated instructors at Scaler Academy!

Register Now

Editors Pick:

How to Change Font and Text Color Using CSS

The presentation of a document written in markup languages such as HTML is described using a style sheet language known as CSS. HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language whereas CSS is the abbreviation for Cascading Style Sheets. They are unique in their syntax. 

Read On

 

Pointers vs References in C++

Pointers and References are confused at the time of implementation because we are not able to distinguish properly between both of them. This is because from the surface both of them seem to be providing us the same functions.

Read On

 

Boolean in C

Computers and other Digital Systems only think in terms of ON(True) or OFF(False), whereas we humans use a very diverse set of symbols in our daily life apart from these two terms. But when there comes a situation to make a decision, we only think in terms of Yes(True) or No(False) statements, which is nothing but a Boolean.

Read On

the best way to build the Metaverse.

At Gather, we believe the Metaverse matters because it will create meaningf=

millions, if not billions of people, no matter where they are.

ther it's conferences, parties, workshops, networking sessions, or socials.=
 We believe this is a huge step up in event quality and overall Gather expe=
rience, and we can't wait for you to see for yourself!

body:
deepnote logo

*********************************
Product updates from Deepnote =E2=9C=A8
*********************************

Happy November! A bunch of exciting features just landed in Deepnote - drag=
 & drop blocks (yes, really), Notion & Deepnote embed experience that just =
feels =F0=9F=92=86 and a chance to win $1k in our competition with spaCy. R=
ead on!

*************************
=F0=9F=8F=82 Drag and drop blocks
*************************

Drag n drop ( https://www.loom.com/share/5662396e3c3b4f909b6b3fcb429728d8 )

We've heard you loud and clear - you can now drag and drop blocks in your n=
otebooks! Stay tuned for more exciting updates that make tinkering with you=
r notebook blocks even more delightful.

************************
Notion + Deepnote =3D =F0=9F=92=99
************************

Notion and Deepnote embedding ( https://www.loom.com/share/41a14b909a5947db=
acc677218a0b5bee )

At Deepnote, we love and live in Notion, but one thing that kept missing wa=
s an analytical layer. So we are bringing Deepnote=E2=80=99s analytical pow=
er right into Notion=E2=80=99s interface. The result is a seamless embeddin=
g experience that allows you to analyze your Notion databases in notebooks,=
 and embed live Deepnote code blocks, data frames and charts back into Noti=
on.

In this article ( https://medium.com/deepnote/bringing-analytics-to-notion-=
with-deepnote-b262a300c6de ) by Liz, you can read more about how our team u=
ses this feature to fuel our productivity, and draw some inspiration for yo=
ur own Notion & Deepnote creations.

*****************************************
=F0=9F=9A=80 spaCy & Deepnote NLP competition
*****************************************

In the last 5 years, spaCy has become an industry standard for NLP. Now spa=
Cy and Deepnote join forces to help you bring the power of NLP into noteboo=
ks. Are you up for the challenge? ( https://deepnote.notion.site/NLP-in-Not=
ebooks-Competition-6616e415f0a44e5c95982e7bc1cb89dd ) Complete one of our t=
asks or build your own showcase using spaCy in notebooks in a creative way.=
 As always, we will reward top 3 submissions with $1,000, $500 and $300 and=
 other cool prizes! The deadline is November 14.

Join the competition ( https://deepnote.notion.site/NLP-in-Notebooks-Compet=
ition-6616e415f0a44e5c95982e7bc1cb89dd )

**********************************
=F0=9F=90=9B Bugfixes & smaller things
**********************************

* We've shipped several smaller improvements around embedding Deepnote bloc=
ks. In addition to Notion, rendering & resizing blocks embedded in Medium i=
s now more intuitive too. Give it a try!

* Deepnote is now available through the Okta store ( https://www.okta.com/i=
ntegrations/deepnote/#overview ) in case you want to set up SSO. =F0=9F=8E=
=89

* We've fixed a bug where part of Deepnote's topbar would hide due to an au=
to-scrolling issue.

* Deepnote now scrolls the window if you are moving up and down in a large =
code block with arrow keys.

* The Deepnote interface got a lot faster. (Just try opening a larger noteb=
ook!)

As always, we would love to see you this Thursday at New in Deepnote demo, =
where we will discuss these latest features and what's coming (RSVP here ( =
https://lu.ma/5oqqgjty )).

I will see you there, and back here in 2 weeks!

Jakub & the Deepnote team =F0=9F=91=8B

=C2=A9 2021 Deepnote, Inc. All rights reserved.

651 N. Broad Street, Suite 206, Middletown, DE 19709, USA

Unsubscribe ( http://track.customer.io/unsubscribe/RISEBgMAAXzinLJ-TAKEkeX9=
Ccsiuw=3D=3D ) from future emails like this.

subject: Notion 2.13
body:
Hi AYUSH,

If I handed you a big bucket of assorted LEGO bricks, how would you separat=
e them into different piles? By color? Shape? Size? Just like LEGOs, your p=
rojects & tasks have different characteristics too: status, importance, urg=
ency...

With Notion 2.13, you can create groups of items in your databases to get o=
rganized on your own terms =E2=80=94 in whatever way makes sense to your br=
ain.

Try it out ( https://www.notion.so/login?utm_campaign=3D2.13+release+email%=
2C+personal%2C+version+A&utm_campaigntype=3Dnewsletter&utm_content=3D2.12+r=
elease+email%2C+personal%2C+version+A&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dcusto=
mer.io )

(1) Create groups in Timeline, Table, List & Gallery views

Click the new Group button to visually organize your content by whatever pr=
operty makes sense for your workflow. Each group includes a toggle to the l=
eft, so you can quickly hide and show groups to focus on what you need.

(2) Create groups and sub-groups in Board view

Already grouping your tasks in Board view? Now you can create sub-groups of=
 those tasks organized by any other property, all while keeping your origin=
al columns intact.

(3) Group by more properties, including Relation properties

Before, you could only group your items based off of Select, Multi-select, =
and Person properties. Now nearly every property type is supported, includi=
ng Relation, Number, Date and more.

(4) More features we launched this month

We're always improving Notion based on your feedback. Here's the latest:

* Bullet lists now default to alternating between discs, circles & squares =
at each level of indentation
* You can now show & hide all database properties with one click in the "Pr=
operties" dropdown menu
* On mobile, tap the =F0=9F=92=AC icon at the top right to see a consolidat=
ed view of comments

(5) Notion is now available in Japanese

We're excited to take a big step toward making Notion feel native and intui=
tive to millions more people. Starting now, Japanese language is available =
in beta!

Go to Settings & members =E2=86=92 Language & region to change your languag=
e on desktop, or your device settings to change your language on mobile.

Learn more =E2=86=92 ( https://www.notion.so/blog/notion-launching-in-japan=
ese?utm_campaign=3D2.13+release+email%2C+personal%2C+version+A&utm_campaign=
type=3Dnewsletter&utm_content=3D2.12+release+email%2C+personal%2C+version+A=
&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io )

Personally, I would sort a big bucket of LEGOs by color, but you might thin=
k about organization differently. That's the beauty of grouping in Notion =
=E2=80=94 everyone can create processes & systems to meet their own needs, =
with more flexibility than ever before.

Wishing you a crisp and restful end to your October, wherever you are.

Warmly,

Ivan

Co-founder & CEO

P.S. We are looking for lots of software engineers, recruiters, sales folks=
 & more ( https://notion.notion.site/Careers-at-Notion-ed4565006f194a2fbe7d=
3a4965d7b15a?utm_campaign=3D2.13+release+email%2C+personal%2C+version+A&utm=
_campaigntype=3Dnewsletter&utm_content=3D2.12+release+email%2C+personal%2C+=

Ramesh,

Ek Coding Challenge jeetne ki keemat kya tum jaante ho Ramesh babu……..

PPO ka aashirwad deta hai ek coding challenge………
CV ke sar ka taj hota hai ek coding challenge……….
Har engineer ka khwab hota hai ek coding challenge………. jeetna!

We know it’s easier said than done to stand out amongst your peers, par woh kehte hain na… ki agar kisi cheez ko dil se chaaho toh puri kayanat usey tumse milane ki koshish mein lag jaati hai. So don’t you worry because this time the kayanat has got you covered.

​ Hi there!

Being a Data Scientist or a Machine Learning Engineer is a prestigious career. Almost every organisation across the globe seeks a team of skilled professionals who can work on their data and help in growing their business. But, when everyone is preparing to become a Data Scientist or a Machine Learning Engineer, how can you stand out from the crowd?

Join Mudit Goel, Product & Strategy Head, Scaler Data Science, in a LIVE Masterclass on October 26, 2021, Tuesday, at 8 PM IST, where you will learn how Scaler Data Science can help you achieve your dream of becoming a Sought-after Data Scientist.

 

Register For Free

 

Key Takeaways From This Masterclass:

  • What defines a Sought-After Data Scientist from the regular ones
  • What is currently missing in Data Science Bootcamps & how Scaler solves that problem
  • Career opportunities in Data Science & Machine Learning disciplines
  • Why Data Science teams of various top companies are willing to hire Scaler graduates

subject: How to Convert Decimal to Binary in Python!
body:
Everything you need to know!
 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ 

Binary is one of the most important foundational aspects of computers and other digital systems. As we humans use languages to understand and communicate with each other, Computers and other Digital Systems use Binary. It is a base-2 number system having only two numbers, 0 & 1 which corresponds to ON & OFF states that your computer can understand.

As normal humans have 10 fingers to represent a simple number system called Decimal, computers have these ON & OFF states representing Binary. So to understand and interpret the binary we need some technique to convert binary code into decimal (human-readable) code and vice versa. Thus in this article, we will discuss how to convert decimal to binary and vice versa, in context with one of the computer programming language-Python.

Understanding Decimal and Binary
Decimal System(Base-10) makes use of ten numbers ranging from 0 to 9 and then uses their combinations to form digits, with each digit being worth ten times more than the last digit (1, 10, 100, so-on) going from left to right.

Consider a value 265:

  • Here 265 is a combination for numbers ranging from 0 to 9 to form each digit
  • Each digit is ten times more than the last digit going from left to right
    5 -> 5×100;  6 -> 6×101;  2 -> 2×102

Binary System(Base-2) is also similar, it is a combination of numbers 0 or 1 with each digit being worth two times more than the last digit(1, 2, 4, so-on) going from left to right.

Decimal Digit Representation:

… [0 to 9] [0 to 9] [0 to 9] [0 to 9] [0 to 9]
… 104 103 102 101 100
Nth digit 5th digit 4th digit 3rd digit 2nd digit 1st digit

Similarly, Binary Digit Representation:

… [0 to 1] [0 to 1] [0 to 1] [0 to 1] [0 to 1]
… 24 23 22 21 20
Nth digit 5th digit 4th digit 3rd digit 2nd digit 1st digit

Binary to Decimal Conversion in Python
We have already seen that the Binary System is a combination of [0 or 1] with each digit being worth two times more than the last digit, so let’s see how this information will help us to convert binary to decimal equivalent.
Consider a Binary Number 01011

Digit 0 1 0 1 1
Weight 24=16 23=8 22=4 21=2 20=1

Hence,
(01011)2 = ( 0x24) + (1×23) + (0x22) + (1×21) + (1×20) =(0) + (8) + (0) + (2) + (1) =(11)10

Therefore, the binary(base-2) (01011)2 is equivalent to (11)10 Decimal(base-10) number.

 

Read On

 

Decimal to Binary Conversion in Python

Let’s try to understand the decimal to binary conversion. The easiest technique to convert the decimal numbers to their binary equivalent is the Division by 2. In Division by 2 technique, we continuously divide a decimal number by 2 and note the reminder, till we get 1 as our input value, and then we read the noted reminders in reverse order to get the final binary value.

Let’s break the earlier statements to get more clarity. Assume we have a special function that divides the input number by 2 and gives the remainder as output. For decimal to binary, we call this special function multiple times till we get the 1 as input value. Then, at last, we print all the saved reminders to get the final binary(base-2) value.

subject: Build your own adventure at GitHub Universe
body:
Space is limited for some sessions and other fun ways to engage ( https://w=
ww.githubuniverse.com/?utm_source=3Dannouncement&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_cam=
paign=3D2021-WW-Dev-Announcement&utm_content=3DWays-to-engage )

GitHub Universe is only a week away. Check out the schedule and start bookm=
arking sessions before it's too late.

The livestream starts at 8 am PDT on October 27 and kicks off with a specia=
l musical performance followed by an opening keynote from GitHub CEO Nat Fr=
iedman at 8:30 am PDT.

Space is limited for interactive sessions following the livestream, so take=
 a look at the schedule ( https://www.githubuniverse.com/2021/schedule?utm_=
source=3Dannouncement&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_campaign=3D2021-WW-Dev-Announc=
ement&utm_content=3DWays-to-engage&utm_cta=3Dschedule ) and save your spot =
now. All on demand sessions will be available following the day 1 keynote. =
Watch the sessions when it works best for you.

View the schedule ( https://www.githubuniverse.com/2021/schedule?utm_source=
=3Dannouncement&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_campaign=3D2021-WW-Dev-Announcement&=
utm_content=3DWays-to-engage&utm_cta=3Dmain )

With over 60 conference sessions, you can build your very own Universe expe=
rience. Get started creating your customized schedule now.

Looking for other fun ways to engage with the global developer community du=
ring Universe? Here are just a few:

* Host a watch party with your friends or colleagues. We=E2=80=99ve put tog=
ether a kit to help you get started, full of tips and tools to experience U=
niverse together
* If you=E2=80=99re tuning in on your own, the Watch Party Kit still includ=
es resources to enhance your Universe experience
* Hop into a virtual focus space, featuring science-backed beats to help yo=
u recharge throughout the event

Head over to githubuniverse.com ( https://www.githubuniverse.com?utm_source=
=3Dannouncement&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_campaign=3D2021-WW-Dev-Announcement&=
utm_content=3DWays-to-engageutm_cta=3Dsite_url ) for more information on ho=
w to create your own personal Universe.

Save your seat ( https://www.githubuniverse.com/?utm_source=3Dannouncement&=
utm_medium=3Demail&utm_campaign=3D2021-WW-Dev-Announcement&utm_content=3DWa=
ys-to-engageutm_cta=3Dsave_your_seat )

See you next week!

subject: Optum's Hiring Challenge, Stratethon is closing its doors in 2 days |  Register now to bag interview offers!
body:
Dear Catalysts,

Optum Stratethon Season 3 is here and it is time to get your game on! 

Optum, part of the UnitedHealth Group family of businesses, is excited to bring you Stratethon Season 3, an international-level challenge for the B-School and E-School students across India, Philippines, Singapore, Hong Kong, Vietnam, and Malaysia. 

Just 2 days are left to join Optum on this journey to help improve the lives of millions around the world and get ready to do your life’s best work.℠

Eligibility Criteria: This challenge is open to full-time 2-year MBA/PGDM students from a select list of B-Schools and full-time B.Tech/B.E. students from select engineering colleges, across specializations.

Rewards & Prizes:

The regional winners from the Business and Engineering track will get prize money worth $6700 each.
The regional runners-up from the Business and Engineering track will get prize money worth $3000 each.
The finalists to receive Pre-Placement Interviews (*subject to Terms & Conditions) at Optum.
All college winners to receive certificates.

Register Now: https://dare2compete.com/p/optum-stratethon-season-3-optum-part-of-unitedhealth-group-216741?refId=OStrat2021S

It is time to balance the scales of the health care sector. Bring your ‘A’ game to do your life’s best work.℠

Best,
Team Optum

subject:
=?utf-8?q?Deepnote_updates=3A_Use_MySQL=2C_Athena_and_Okta_in_De?=
 =?utf-8?b?ZXBub3RlIPCfp7Y=?=
body:
deepnote logo

*********************************
Product updates from Deepnote =E2=9C=A8
*********************************

Happy October! Today, we're announcing exciting new integrations in Deepnot=
e - you can now connect to your MySQL and Amazon Athena instances and use t=
hem to bring SQL into your notebooks. We're also launching Okta integration=
 and a new way to sort your projects.

As always, if you'd like to get a demo of the new features, join us for the=
 New in Deepnote session on Thursday, November 4 at 9am PT / 4pm UTC (RSVP =
here ( https://lu.ma/5oqqgjty )). Let's dive in!

**********************************
=F0=9F=90=AC Connect to MySQL & Athena
**********************************

MySQL + Athena integrations screenshot

Our list of integrations is growing! You can now connect to your MySQL and =
Amazon Athena instances and query data with SQL cells, right within your no=
tebook. This is a powerful feature - when you run SQL queries in Deepnote, =
you can assign and store resulting dataframes in Python variables, and use =
advanced templating blocks inside of SQL. Take it for a spin - in this vide=
o ( https://www.loom.com/share/d0648e093df744ccac8cad4b4351c31f ), Liz show=
s you how!

You can find the full list of existing integrations and tutorials on how to=
 use them here ( https://deepnote.com/integrations ).

**************************
=F0=9F=94=93 Sign in with Okta SSO
**************************

Okta integration screenshot

Deepnote now integrates with Okta for a more secure sign-in process. If you=
'd like to enable it for your team or organization, you can learn more abou=
t the set up process here ( https://docs.deepnote.com/resources/okta-sso ).

This feature is exclusive to Deepnote Enterprise plan users. You can learn =
more about our full offering and schedule a live demo here ( https://deepno=
te.com/pricing ).

************************************
=F0=9F=A7=BD Sort projects in your dashboard
************************************

sorting projects screenshot
You can now sort projects in your dashboard by recent edits or time they we=
re created. No more scrolling through stale or old projects!

**********************************
=F0=9F=90=9B Bugfixes & smaller things
**********************************

* We have increased the allowed runtime of published projects to 2 minutes.=
 Do let us know if you still happen to run into difficulties here!
* Projects will no longer keep running when your browser tab is open. This =
means that a project will be shut down if there is no activity for 15 minut=
es (i.e., code execution or editing). If you are using out non-standard mac=
hines ( https://docs.deepnote.com/resources/pricing#machines-hardware ), yo=
u can customize or prolong the inactivity period. You can read more about u=
pdates in runtime conditions in our docs ( https://docs.deepnote.com/enviro=
nment/long-running-jobs ).
* We have added the option to import your project from Google Drive when yo=
u create a new notebook.

* If you hover over a cell, you will now see an option to add a new comment=
 on the top right.

* When the load on our infrastructure is high, we will let you know via an =
in-app message that scheduling a new machine for your project might take a =
bit more time.

* We fixed the bug where pressing Escape did not close the underlying modal=
 or dialog, but instead opened the Command Palette ( https://docs.deepnote.=
com/features/command-palette ).

Have a great weekend & see you back here in 2 weeks!
Jakub & the Deepnote team =F0=9F=91=8B

=C2=A9 2021 Deepnote, Inc. All rights reserved.

651 N. Broad Street, Suite 206, Middletown, DE 19709, USA
